  ECHO OTHERS %n inhales deeply as %s lights %a.
ENDIF
;
; Guide
INUMBER 950
NAME 422
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
PARAMETER1 1
SUBSTANCE PAPER
WIELDABLE
*DESCRIPTION_START READ
Since you can't judge a book by its cover, perhaps you should open it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS %N flips through the pages of %h %a.
  ECHO PLAYER You flip through the pages of the guide and read the following:%c%
  IFVAR RNUM = 1615
    ECHO PLAYER "Ask yourself for HELP when you can't COMMAND the world at your will."%c%c     - Drex Nabius
  ENDIF
  IFVAR RNUM = 1608
    ECHO PLAYER "Sometimes things are not as they appear."%c%c     - The Great Universal They
  ENDIF
  IFVAR RNUM ! 1608
    IFVAR RNUM ! 1615
      RANDOM DUMMY4 1 21 0
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 14
        ECHO PLAYER "An adventurer never whines, especially to the gods."%c%c     - Selene Morgause
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 2
        ECHO PLAYER "It is generally important to search every nook and cranny... ...never leave a stone unturned"%c%c     The Great Universal They
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 3
        ECHO PLAYER "Things are not always as they seem, when you are stuck, try to look at the problem in every way you can."%c%c     - Magnifico the Magnific
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 4
        ECHO PLAYER "1. Keep a firm grasp on your weapon;%c 2. Keep one eye on your back; and%c 3. Always pay your death insurance."%c%c     - Drex Nabius
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 5
        ECHO PLAYER "When you are sure you have done everything, do it all again a different way."%c%c     - Drex Nabius
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 6
        ECHO PLAYER "Never assume you know how something works just because you got one result one time."%c%c     - Drex Nabius
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 7
        ECHO PLAYER "In a magical world, empirical analysis is often invalid."%c%c     - Tarinth Lintaranz
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 8
        ECHO PLAYER "There is no pleasure without pain."%c%c      - Book of Shaltos
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 9
        ECHO PLAYER "To do nothing, is in every man's power."%c%c     - Samual Johnson
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 10
        ECHO PLAYER "To attempt an adventure without adequate roots, berries, lockpicks, torches and potions is a good way to insure disaster."%c%c     - Drex Nabius
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 11
        ECHO PLAYER "The best way to attract treasure and wealth into your life is to have some room in your pack to carry it."%c%c     - Fernil Stonehand
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 12
        ECHO PLAYER "One can always hope for the best advice when consulting a Scholar of Fayd."%c%c     - Phelan Kell
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 13
        ECHO PLAYER "If you don't read the room descriptions you will probably die as well you should."%c%c     - Selene Morgause
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 1
        ECHO PLAYER "It is always best to do some advance recon of an area before charging into it headfirst.%c%c     - Zerek Von Slek, aelfen scout
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 15
        ECHO PLAYER "If at first you don't succeed, try, try again."%c%c     - The Great Universal They
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 16
        ECHO PLAYER "It is always amazing what people will just throw away, and amazing how fortunate I am at finding it."%c%c     - Fernil Stonehand
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 17
        ECHO PLAYER "Be a friend to your white necromancers: carry a little mandrake root at all times."%c%c     - Yshtarin
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 18
        ECHO PLAYER "Nothing beats a warhammer for sheer destruction."%c%c - Drex Nabius
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 19
        ECHO PLAYER "If one does not parse, one is an arse."%c%c - Selene Morgause
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 20
        ECHO PLAYER "Ask yourself for HELP when you can't COMMAND the world at your will."%c%c     - Drex Nabius
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY4 = 21
        ECHO PLAYER "Sometimes things are not as they appear."%c%c     - The Great Universal They
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
  ECHO PLAYER %c[Round: 5 sec]
ENDIF
